# =============================================================================
# Environment Variables for Cancer Early Detection Pipeline
# =============================================================================
#
# LLM CONFIGURATION (Multi-Agent Clinical Reasoning)
# ---------------------------------------------------
# The pipeline uses a priority chain:
#   1. Groq  (FREE & open-source) ← RECOMMENDED
#   2. OpenAI
#   3. Mock fallback (no LLM reasoning, just ML models)
#
# ✅ OPTION 1 — Groq (FREE, uses LLaMA 3.3 70B)
#    Get your free key at: https://console.groq.com
#    No credit card needed. Generous free tier.
#
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here
#
# Models available on Groq (free tier):
#   - llama-3.3-70b-versatile  ← best for clinical reasoning
#   - llama-3.1-70b-versatile
#   - mixtral-8x7b-32768
#   - gemma2-9b-it
#
# ✅ OPTION 2 — OpenAI (paid)
#    Only set this if you have an OpenAI account.
#
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here
#
# =============================================================================
# USAGE:
#   Windows PowerShell:  $env:GROQ_API_KEY="your_key"
#   Windows CMD:         set GROQ_API_KEY=your_key
#   Linux/Mac:           export GROQ_API_KEY=your_key
# =============================================================================
